can the ones already in heaven see or know what is going on here on earth it is scary to think of my grandparents seeing the world as it is today i would be ashamed for them to see the things happening in today's world the bible does not specifically say whether people can look down on us who are still on the earth it is highly likely that they cannot why one they would sometimes witness us sinning two they would sometimes see things that would cause them grief three people in heaven are so occupied with worshipping god and enjoying the glories of heaven that they truly have no interest in what is happening here on earth the very fact that they are free from sin in heaven and in god s presence is enough for them to be happy while it is possible that god allows people in heaven to look down upon their loved ones the bible gives us no reason to believe this actually occurs recommended resource what the bible says about heaven eternity by ice demy Heaven Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism A Course In Miracles God Sabbath Ten Commandments Original sin Doctrines of Jehovah's Witnesses Eastern Orthodox Church Christianity Abrahamic religion Idolatry Duties of the Heart Jehovah's Witnesses Divine grace Satan Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Soul Merit Predestination Paradise Lost Trinity End times Devil Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief Religion Resurrection of Jesus Fallen angel Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Summa Theologiae Hell Calvinism Angel Creationism Book of Isaiah Salvation Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Miracle Book of Mormon Dispensationalism Mary, the mother of Jesus Tribulation Revelation Origin belief Catholicism Sola fide Sant Thakar Singh Rich Mullins Church of Christ, Scientist Church of Christ Theodicy Justification (theology) Armageddon Urantia Rapture Eschatology Problem of Hell John Wycliffe Purgatory Sin Pascal's Wager Humility Prophet Israel ben Eliezer Salvation Army Supernatural Storytel